cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.CV

This paper is about improving neural machine translation (NMT) systems, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes and compares several models for fusion of bilingual lexicons with an end-to-end trained sequence-to-sequence model, which involves machine learning techniques such as neural networks and optimization algorithms. This suggests that cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Learning) are also likely sub-categories. Additionally, the paper mentions reducing the parameter size and training cost for NMT, which could fall under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper uses some image examples to illustrate the effectiveness of the proposed models, which could suggest a connection to cs.CV (Computer Vision).
